      "content": "No, \"Goblin's Whisper\" is just a colloquialism I like to use to illustrate the concept of entanglement. It's not a formal theory, but more of a metaphor to help grasp the idea of non-local correlation. You see, in a classical sense, information can only travel at a finite speed, so if two particles are separated, they can't affect each other instantly. But with entanglement, it's as if the information is being transmitted through some kind of... mystical, goblin-like channel. It's a bit of a stretch, I know, but it can help make the abstract concept more tangible.",
